Actress Mercy Johnson Okojie has described giving everybody access to one’s self as poor spiritual hygiene. In a video posted by the mother of four via her Instagram page, she relayed her message through a voice playing in the background and inscription on the clip while she made head gestures in agreement. She argued not everyone is worthy to enjoy the privilege adding, it must be treated with a great sense of value.   Agitation for Biafra beyond Kanu, says IPOB     Why PDP can’t rule Lagos, by Oladejo     Mason Greenwood: End of glorious career?   The clip’s inscription reads: “It is poor spiritual hygiene to give everybody access to you. Access to you is a privilege, you got to treat it like it’s golden.” - Advertisement - In captioning her post, the 37-year-old entrepreneur prayed for the uncovering of evil persons being innocently harboured in homes. “A person can live in your home, and still speak/plan evil against you. May God always exposes them through their most trusted,” she wrote.